post_text: Please review the following letter for an important update on the return to school. #atlanticcitypublicschools
text: Please review the following letter for an important update on the return to school. #atlanticcitypublicschools

post_text:
Hello Parents and Guardians,

This is Michael Bird, Director of Assessments and Special Projects for Atlantic City Public Schools. We hope this message finds you and your families doing well. As we continue to adapt to the current times it is critical that all parents and guardians receive information quickly. To ensure that this is occurring the Atlantic City Public School system will be moving away from paper mailings and moving towards communicating with you electronically. To ensure that you are part of receiving all critical information please go to www.acboe.org and click on the ‚ÄúBack to School Registration‚Äù link located on the main page. Parents and guardians will need to enter their child's student ID# as the username and their child's date of birth (mm/dd/yyyy) as the password. Please use this portal to provide a current phone number and email address. The first electronic mailing will be your child‚Äôs report card from the 2019-2020 school year. We thank you in advance for updating your information. Please enjoy the rest of your summer.

post_text:
Hello Parents:

The Atlantic City Public Schools and the City of Atlantic City are offering a free Esports Virtual Recreation League. Parents who have students in 6th through 12th grade can choose from Madden 20 or NBA2k. All those who are interested must go to www.metrotech.gg and click the register button and use register code:958672.

Parents who have students in kindergarten through 5th grade can participate in Minecraft. Click AC Minecraft on the metrotech.gg website.

Academic scholarship prizes will be awarded to winning participants. Get more details by following METROESPORTS on Instagram and Twitter or click on the Virtual Recreation link at www.acboe.org.

post_text:
Hello!! This is Barry Caldwell, Superintendent of Atlantic City Schools, calling to inform you that in order to more safely and efficiently distribute breakfast and lunch meals, the following changes to distribution go into effect tomorrow, Monday, May 11th.

Monday: Students will receive breakfast/lunch for Monday and Tuesday (2 days).

Wednesday: Students will receive breakfast/lunch for Wednesday and Thursday (2 days).

Friday: Students will receive breakfast/lunch for Friday, Saturday and Sunday (3 days).

Please be ready to collect the extra bags and store them at home for freshness. Such changes to distribution will lessen the number of trips for pick-up and will provide food for weekends.

We hope that this will be a help to students and their families during the COVID-19 Pandemic.

post_text:
Good Evening Parents:

This is Atlantic City High School calling to let you know that we miss our students every day and we hope that all of our families are healthy and safe. Please make note of the following announcements:

First, please be reminded that Parent Teacher conferences scheduled this week will be ongoing. Teachers are making every effort to contact parents to provide an update of your child‚Äôs performance; however, if there is an immediate concern, please contact your child‚Äôs teacher via email.

Secondly, please access the updated letter to parents on our district‚Äôs website to view the district‚Äôs revised instructional plan.
Lastly, please remind your students that signing in with their homeroom teacher is mandatory. It is imperative that we account for child‚Äôs participation.
Remember, we are here if you need us. Please check the school and district websites for updates and do not hesitate to contact your child‚Äôs teacher, counselor or administrator, if you have any concerns.
Have a wonderful evening!

post_text:
Good Evening Parents and Guardians,

This is Assistant Superintendent Sherry Yahn calling to remind you that remote instruction will resume tomorrow, Monday April 20th.
We hope that you and your family are safe, healthy and faring well throughout the continued directive to say home.Please be advised that Governor Murphy has extended the closing of schools until May 15th at which time he will provide information regarding the remainder of the school year. Visit the Atlantic City Board of Education website for COVID-19 related updates and Atlantic City Public Schools‚Äô remote instruction updates.

post_text:
Good Evening Parents and Guardians,

This is Dr. Davis, Principal of Uptown School Complex calling to remind you that our winter break begins on Tuesday, December 24th. We will have a half day on December 23rd. It may be tempting to extend the vacation by a few days, but please remember those days count as absences. Absences affect your child and our overall school performance.

Just a few missed days here and there can add up to too much lost learning time. So please make sure your child is in school every day right up until vacation starts. We also want to make sure that your child returns to school on January 2nd, which will be a full day.

Our teachers will be teaching, and our students will be learning. Please enjoy this holiday season and contact the main office with any questions or concerns.

post_text: Good evening, this is Barry Caldwell, Superintendent of Atlantic City Schools. On behalf of the entire staff, I would like to wish you and your family a joyous holiday season. As a reminder, all schools will be dismissed early on Monday December 23rd and begin winter recess on Tuesday December 24th thru Wednesday January 1st. Schools will resume their normal schedules on Thursday January 2nd. I hope all of you have a happy and healthy holiday and are able to spend some quality time with family, friends and loved ones. I want to personally thank you for your support throughout the school year. It has been a great year and we look forward to 2020. Have a happy holiday and a safe and wonderful New Year. Thank you

text: Good evening, this is Barry Caldwell, Superintendent of Atlantic City Schools. On behalf of the entire staff, I would like to wish you and your family a joyous holiday season. As a reminder, all schools will be dismissed early on Monday December 23rd and begin winter recess on Tuesday December 24th thru Wednesday January 1st. Schools will resume their normal schedules on Thursday January 2nd. I hope all of you have a happy and healthy holiday and are able to spend some quality time with family, friends and loved ones. I want to personally thank you for your support throughout the school year. It has been a great year and we look forward to 2020. Have a happy holiday and a safe and wonderful New Year. Thank you

post_text:
Good Evening Parents and Guardians,

This is Dr. Davis, Principal of Uptown School Complex calling to remind you that our winter break begins on Tuesday, December 24th. We will have a half day on December 23rd. It may be tempting to extend the vacation by a few days, but please remember those days count as absences. Absences affect your child and our overall school performance.

Just a few missed days here and there can add up to too much lost learning time. So please make sure your child is in school every day right up until vacation starts. We also want to make sure that your child returns to school on January 2nd, which will be a full day.

Our teachers will be teaching, and our students will be learning. Please enjoy this holiday season and contact the main office with any questions or concerns.
